{"parse":{"title":"banana boat","pageid":1876669,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{wp}}\n[[Image:Banana Boat Beras Basah.JPG|thumb|Women on a '''banana boat''' in Indonesia]]\n[[Image:Banana boat.jpg|thumb|A '''banana boat''' dessert]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Flame, not lame-banana boat.wav|a=US}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|nautical}} An [[inflatable]] recreational [[boat]] meant for [[towing]], often yellow and banana-shaped.\n# {{lb|en|nautical}} A [[ship]] designed to transport [[banana]]s.\n# A [[cocktail]] made from a [[melon]] [[liqueur]], a [[banana]] liqueur, [[curacao]]{{,}} and [[pineapple juice]].\n# {{lb|en|US|slang}} The group of {{w|National Basketball Association|NBA}} players {{w|Carmelo Anthony}}, {{w|LeBron James}}, {{w|Chris Paul}} and {{w|Dwyane Wade}}.\n# {{lb|en|derogatory|figurative}} A [[vessel]] which transports [[immigrants]].\n# A [[dessert]] or [[campfire]] [[snack]] consisting of an [[unpeeled]] banana cut [[lengthwise]] and stuffed with [[marshmallow]]s and [[chocolate]] before being [[cook]]ed.\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|boat meant for towing, often yellow and banana-shaped}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|bananbåd|c}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|banan|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|ship for transporting bananas}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|bananiera|f}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|bananbåt}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|bananowiec|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{C|en|Cocktails|Watercraft}}\n{{cln|en|alliterative compounds}}"}}